# Phase 32: Schedule Overhaul & Double-Booking Prevention

Major overhaul of the Appointments screen, booking flow, and schedule card interactions based on 8 detailed user requirements.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a large overhaul that will **completely rewrite** [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart) (~667 lines) and significantly modify [create_appointment_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart) (~695 lines), [patient_info_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/patient_info_screen.dart) (310 lines), and [appointment_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart). Please review carefully.

> [!WARNING]
> The phone number will become the **unique patient identifier** for double-booking prevention. Patients with no phone number stored will not trigger duplicate checks.

## Proposed Changes

### Component 1: Double-Booking Prevention & Auto-Fill

#### [MODIFY] [create_appointment_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart)

**Phone-based duplicate detection (Call-By):**
- Add an `onChanged` listener to `_phoneCtrl` that debounces (500ms) and queries PocketBase for:
  1. **Existing patient record** matching phone → prompt "Patient already exists. Auto-fill details?" → pre-fill name, DOB, address, etc.
  2. **Existing scheduled appointment** for the same doctor on the same/selected date → show warning dialog: "An appointment is already scheduled for this patient: [Date] at [Time]. Replace it?" with option to cancel or replace.
- For Walk-In: same phone check logic applies — warn if patient already has scheduled appointment today.

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_service.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/core/services/appointment_service.dart)

- Add `Future<PatientModel?> findPatientByPhone(String phone, String doctorId)` — queries patients collection by phone.
- Add `Future<AppointmentModel?> findExistingAppointment(String phone, String doctorId, String date)` — queries appointments by `patient_phone` + doctor + date + status=scheduled.

---

### Component 2: Schedule Cards Split (Consultation vs Session)

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart)

**Complete rewrite of the list body:**
- Replace the single flat list with **two collapsible sections**:
  1. **📋 Consultations** — appointments where `type == call_by || type == walk_in`
  2. **💊 Sessions** — appointments where `type == session`
- Each section has its own header with count badge and a `ListView` of cards.
- Both sections are visible simultaneously (no tabs), separated by a styled divider.

---

### Component 3: Redesigned Schedule Cards

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart)

**New card layout with rich interactions:**

- **Header row**: Patient name, type badge (Call-By / Walk-In / Session), scheduled time.
- **Late indicator**: If `status == scheduled` AND current time > appointment time on the same day → show pulsing red "⏰ Patient Late" badge.
- **"Patient Arrived" button**: Large, prominent green button visible when `status == scheduled`. On tap:
  - Records `check_in_time` = `DateTime.now()`.
  - Updates status to `in_progress`.
  - Refreshes the card to reveal the "Fill Details" button.
  - For Walk-In: the initial form submission already serves as check-in, so this button is **hidden** for walk-ins (walk-in form submission = check-in).
- **"Fill Details" button**: Only visible after patient has arrived (status=in_progress, check_in_time set). Tapping opens [PatientInfoScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/patient_info_screen.dart#13-21).
- **"Appointment Ended" button**: Only visible after patient details are filled (i.e., `patientId` is linked/non-empty). On tap:
  - Records `check_out_time` = `DateTime.now()`.
  - Updates status to `completed`.
- **Cancel via Long Press**: Remove the inline cancel icon. Instead, `onLongPress` on the card shows a confirmation dialog to cancel the appointment.
- **Tap to Patient Profile**: Regular `onTap` on the card navigates to the patient's profile in the Patients tab (if `patientId` is linked).

---

### Component 4: Walk-In Arrival Logic

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart)

- Walk-in appointments already have `check_in_time` set on creation and `status=in_progress`.
- So the "Patient Arrived" button is automatically **not shown** for walk-ins.
- Walk-ins only need the "Appointment Ended" button (same mechanism).

---

### Component 5: Patient Profile Navigation

#### [MODIFY] [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart)

- On card tap: If `patientId` is set, navigate to `/patient-profile` with the patient record.
- If `patientId` is not set (call-by before arrival), show a snackbar: "Patient hasn't arrived yet."

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `flutter analyze` to confirm zero errors.
- Hot-reload and test each card state transition manually.

### Manual Verification
1. **Call-By flow**: Create call-by → see card with "Patient Arrived" button → tap Arrived → see "Fill Details" → fill form → see "Appointment Ended" → tap to complete.
2. **Walk-In flow**: Create walk-in → card shows directly with "Appointment Ended" button (check_in already recorded).
3. **Double-booking**: Enter same phone twice for call-by → see warning with existing appointment details.
4. **Late indicator**: Create appointment for a past time slot today → verify red "Patient Late" badge appears.
5. **Long-press cancel**: Long-press a scheduled card → confirm cancel dialog.
6. **Tap navigation**: Tap a linked card → verify it opens PatientProfileScreen.
